--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
---CHUNK---
Document: InputEventMIDI
Path: godot/classes/class_inputeventmidi.rst
Summary: Represents a MIDI message from a MIDI device.

InputEventMIDI
Inherits: InputEvent < Resource < RefCounted < Object

Represents a MIDI message from a MIDI device, such as a musical keyboard.
---CHUNK---
Document: InputEventMIDI
Path: godot/classes/class_inputeventmidi.rst
Summary: Stores information about MIDI messages from devices and provides examples of how to handle them in GDScript and C#.
Inherits: InputEvent < Resource < RefCounted < Object
InputEventMIDI stores information about messages from MIDI (Musical Instrument Digital Interface) devices, such as musical keyboards, synthesizers, and drum machines. These messages can be received over a 5-pin MIDI connector or USB.

By default, Godot does not detect MIDI devices. To enable MIDI input, you must first call OS.open_midi_inputs(). You can check which devices are detected with OS.get_connected_midi_inputs() and close the connection with OS.close_midi_inputs().

GDScript:
```gdscript
func _ready():
    OS.open_midi_inputs()
    print(OS.get_connected_midi_inputs())

func _input(input_event):
    if input_event is InputEventMIDI:
        _print_midi_info(input_event)

func _print_midi_info(midi_event):
    print(midi_event)
    print("Channel ", midi_event.channel)
    print("Message ", midi_event.message)
    print("Pitch ", midi_event.pitch)
    print("Velocity ", midi_event.velocity)
    print("Instrument ", midi_event.instrument)
    print("Pressure ", midi_event.pressure)
    print("Controller number: ", midi_event.controller_number)
    print("Controller value: ", midi_event.controller_value)
```

C#:
```csharp
public override void _Ready()
{
    OS.OpenMidiInputs();
    GD.Print(OS.GetConnectedMidiInputs());
}

public override void _Input(InputEvent inputEvent)
{
    if (inputEvent is InputEventMidi midiEvent)
    {
        PrintMIDIInfo(midiEvent);
    }
}

private void PrintMIDIInfo(InputEventMidi midiEvent)
{
    GD.Print(midiEvent);
    GD.Print($"Channel {midiEvent.Channel}");
    GD.Print($"Message {midiEvent.Message}");
    GD.Print($"Pitch {midiEvent.Pitch}");
    GD.Print($"Velocity {midiEvent.Velocity}");
    GD.Print($"Instrument {midiEvent.Instrument}");
    GD.Print($"Pressure {midiEvent.Pressure}");
    GD.Print($"Controller number: {midiEvent.ControllerNumber}");
    GD.Print($"Controller value: {midiEvent.ControllerValue}");
}
```

Note: Godot does not support MIDI output, so there is no way to emit MIDI messages from Godot. Only MIDI input is supported.

Note: On the Web platform, using MIDI input requires a browser permission to be granted first. This permission request is performed when calling OS.open_midi_inputs(). MIDI input will not work until the user accepts the permission request.
---CHUNK---
Document: InputEventMIDI
Path: godot/classes/class_inputeventmidi.rst
Summary: This document describes the InputEventMIDI class in Godot Engine, which represents MIDI input events.

Inherits: InputEvent < RefCounted < Object

InputEventMIDI

A MIDI input event.

Properties
- channel (int): The MIDI channel (0-15).
- command (int): The MIDI command (e.g., note on, note off, program change). See MIDI command constants.
- data1 (int): The first data byte of the MIDI message. Typically used for note pitch or controller number.
- data2 (int): The second data byte of the MIDI message. Typically used for velocity or controller value.
- velocity (int): Alias for data2 when the command is a note on/off event.

Methods
- get_channel() → int: Returns the MIDI channel.
- get_command() → int: Returns the MIDI command.
- get_data1() → int: Returns the first data byte.
- get_data2() → int: Returns the second data byte.
- get_velocity() → int: Returns the velocity (alias for data2 for note on/off events).

Constants
MIDI command constants:

- COMMAND_NOTE_OFF: 128
- COMMAND_NOTE_ON: 144
- COMMAND_AFTERTOUCH: 160
- COMMAND_CONTROL_CHANGE: 176
- COMMAND_PROGRAM_CHANGE: 192
- COMMAND_PITCH_BEND: 224
- COMMAND_AFTERTOUCH_POLYPHONY: 160
- COMMAND_CHANNEL_PRESSURE: 160
- COMMAND_SYSTEM_EXCLUSIVE: 240
- COMMAND_MIDI_TIME_CODE: 241
- COMMAND_SONG_POSITION: 242
- COMMAND_SONG_SELECT: 243
- COMMAND_TUNE_REQUEST: 246
- COMMAND_CLOCK: 248
- COMMAND_START: 250
- COMMAND_CONTINUE: 251
- COMMAND_STOP: 252
- COMMAND_SENSING: 254
- COMMAND_RESET: 255

Note: Some commands share the same integer value. The actual command can be determined by checking the data bytes or context.

Example Usage:

GDScript:
```gdscript
func _input(event):
	if event is InputEventMIDI:
		print("MIDI Event:")
		print("  Channel: ", event.channel)
		print("  Command: ", event.command)
		print("  Data1: ", event.data1)
		print("  Data2: ", event.data2)

		if event.command == InputEventMIDI.COMMAND_NOTE_ON:
			print("  Note On Velocity: ", event.velocity)
		elif event.command == InputEventMIDI.COMMAND_CONTROL_CHANGE:
			print("  Controller Number: ", event.data1)
			print("  Controller Value: ", event.data2)
```
---CHUNK---
Document: InputEventMIDI
Path: godot/classes/class_inputeventmidi.rst
Summary: Defines the properties available for MIDI input events in Godot.

Properties:
* channel (int): The MIDI channel the event occurred on. Default: 0
* controller_number (int): The controller number for a controller change message. Default: 0
* controller_value (int): The value of the controller for a controller change message. Default: 0
* instrument (int): The instrument number for a program change message. Default: 0
* message (MIDIMessage): The type of MIDI message. Default: 0
* pitch (int): The pitch value for a note on/off message. Default: 0
* pressure (int): The pressure value for a channel aftertouch message. Default: 0
* velocity (int): The velocity value for a note on/off message. Default: 0
---CHUNK---
Document: InputEventMIDI
Path: godot/classes/class_inputeventmidi.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of an InputEventMIDI object, which represents MIDI input events in Godot.

Property: channel
Type: int
Default: 0
Description: The MIDI channel of this message, ranging from 0 to 15. MIDI channel 9 is reserved for percussion instruments.

Property: controller_number
Type: int
Default: 0
Description: The unique number of the controller, if message is MIDI_MESSAGE_CONTROL_CHANGE, otherwise this is 0. This value can be used to identify sliders for volume, balance, and panning, as well as switches and pedals on the MIDI device.

Property: controller_value
Type: int
Default: 0
Description: The value applied to the controller. If message is MIDI_MESSAGE_CONTROL_CHANGE, this value ranges from 0 to 127, otherwise it is 0.

Property: instrument
Type: int
Default: 0
Description: The instrument (also called program or preset) used on this MIDI message. This value ranges from 0 to 127. A value of 0 corresponds to the acoustic grand piano.

Property: message
Type: MIDIMessage
Default: 0
Description: Represents the type of MIDI message (see the MIDIMessage enum).

Property: pitch
Type: int
Default: 0
Description: The pitch index number of this MIDI message. This value ranges from 0 to 127. On a piano, the middle C is 60, followed by a C-sharp (61), then a D (62), and so on. Each octave is split in offsets of 12.

Property: pressure
Type: int
Default: 0
Description: The strength of the key being pressed. This value ranges from 0 to 127. Note: For many devices, this value is always 0. Other devices such as musical keyboards may simulate pressure by changing the velocity, instead.

Property: velocity
Type: int
Default: 0
Description: The velocity of the MIDI message. This value ranges from 0 to 127. For a musical keyboard, this corresponds to how quickly the key was pressed, and is rarely above 110 in practice. Note: Some MIDI devices may send a MIDI_MESSAGE_NOTE_ON message with 0 velocity and expect it to be treated the same as a MIDI_MESSAGE_NOTE_OFF message. If necessary, this can be handled with a few lines of code:
GDScript:
    func _input(event):
        if event is InputEventMIDI:
            if event.message == MIDI_MESSAGE_NOTE_ON and event.velocity > 0:
                print("Note pressed!")